title: 'Billy on the Street' proves New Yorkers don't know Chris Pratt
text:
'Billy on the Street' proves New Yorkers don't know Chris Pratt 
Margaret Lenker, Variety.com Monday, October 12, 2015 06:38 PM CDT | Updated: Monday, October 12, 2015 06:54 PM CDT Chris Pratt, left, and comedian Billy Eichner took to the streets of NYC for the upcoming episode of his rapid-fire "Billy on the Street." (truTV/YouTube) Report an error 
LOS ANGELES - Chris Pratt may be known in Hollywood for roles in "Jurassic World,""Guardians of the Galaxy" and "Parks and Recreation," but it seems New Yorkers don't know him at all. Emmy-nominated comedian Billy Eichner took to the streets of NYC with Pratt for the upcoming episode of his rapid-fire "Billy on the Street." 
Eichner catches pedestrians off guard when he quickly introduces them to Pratt and asks if they can identify him. In the preview, only one woman actually knows Pratt, while others are completely clueless. 
"Billy on the Street," previously on Fuse, premiered on TruTV in the U.S. last week. The full episode featuring Pratt will air 10:30 p.m. on Thursday.
